===Noun===
'''ball''' (''plural'' [[balls]])

# Any roughly spherical object.
# An object, generally spherical, used for playing games.
# (''baseball'') A pitch that falls outside the strike zone.
# (''pinball'') An opportunity to launch the ball into play.
# (''mathematics'') The set of points in a [[metric space]] lying within a given distance (the [[radius]]) of a given point; specifically, the [[homologue]] of the [[disk]] in any a [[Euclidean space]] of any number of dimensions.
# (''vulgar slang''; ''usually in plural'') A testicle.
# A formal dance.
# (''colloquial'') A very enjoyable time.
#:''I had a ball at that concert''

====Synonyms====
*(''roughly spherical object''): [[sphere]]
*(''testicle''): [[bollock]], [[nut]]
